 According to Gugu Ncube, her husband, who is a sangoma, “was led by his ancestors to the foetus”.
The foetus was discovered at the back of a house, in a plastic bag. She told www.mobserver.co.za that she thought the plastic bag contained raw meat, but after careful observation, they noticed a head and legs.
The gender of the foetus is unknown. The foetus was removed from the scene by the state pathologists. • Earlier this year Francis Davis launched Middelburg’s first baby safe. The Precious Life Baby Project, situated at the St John’s Presbyterian Church, aims to give women alternatives to abortion.  Hawks members sent to jail for fraud WATCH: The Place of Refuge – Once a vibrant village, now a ghost town WATCH: Robbery caught on video, police looking for suspects Three counts of poaching in one week – and the toll keeps rising   • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za